     This is a static webpage for the scholarship application form. Here we used some HTML tags, CSS style properties, and Javascript. 
in this website we are giving information regarding our scholarships like the documents required, Eligibility criteria, and login page.

    We have used our learnings of web development learned in our modules, i.e. 
basic usage of HTML tags and CSS styling methods, and Javascript to design this webpage.

as per my knowledge i created my own website and here by below shown my code
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Facebook Login</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="fb.css">
    <script type="text/javascript">
        function msg(){
                                    alert("Login Successful");
                                   }
        function message(){
                                   alert("Recovery Mail sent to your Email ID");
                                          }
    </script>
</head>
<body>
    <center>
<img src="https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/rsrc.php/y8/r/dF5SId3UHWd.svg" height="90" class="facebook"  
</center>
    <div class="container">
        
        <form>
            
            <center><h1>Log in to Facebook</h1></center>
            <div class="form-group">
                <label>Email address or phone number</label>
                <input type="text" class="form-control"           placeholder="Email address or phone number">
            </div>
            <div class="form-group">
                <label>Password</label>
                <input type="password" class="form-   control"  placeholder="Password">
            </div>
            <input type="button" class="btn btn-primary" value="Log In" onclick="msg()"/>
                <div class="forgot-password">
              <a href="#" onclick="message()">Forgot Password?</a>
                <a href="#">Sign up for Facebook </a>
            
            </div>
        </form>
    </div>
</body>
</html>


